#: ../../P/pizza-box.rst:5
msgid "pizza box"
msgstr "pizza box"

#: ../../P/pizza-box.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../P/pizza-box.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Sun] The largish thin box housing the electronics in (especially Sun) "
"desktop workstations, so named because of its size and shape and the dimpled"
" pattern that looks like air holes."
msgstr ""
"[Sun](特にSunの)デスクトップワークステーションの電子部品を収める、やや大きめの薄い箱。その大きさと形、そして空気穴のように見えるくぼみ模様から、そう名付けられた。"

#: ../../P/pizza-box.rst:11
msgid ""
"Two-meg single-platter removable disk packs used to be called pizzas, and "
"the huge drive they were stuck into was referred to as a pizza oven. It's an"
" index of progress that in the old days just the disk was pizza-sized, while"
" now the entire computer is."
msgstr ""
"2メガの単一プラッタのリムーバブルディスクパックは、かつてpizzaと呼ばれ、それが差し込まれる巨大なドライブはpizza "
"ovenと呼ばれた。昔はディスクだけがピザサイズだったのに、今ではコンピュータ全体がそうだというのは、進歩の指標である。"
